<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A large established family suburb with strong owner-occupier fundamentals.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Kenmore sits approximately 12 kilometres west of the CBD, positioned along the Moggill Road corridor between Indooroopilly to the east and the semi-rural outer western suburbs beyond. It is a large suburb with a clear identity: generous blocks, quiet leafy residential streets, a high proportion of owner-occupiers who have raised families here, and a school catchment that continues to drive serious buyer interest. Kenmore Hills, the elevated pocket on the western side, adds views and a slightly more private semi-rural character to the mix.
    </p>
